sentences: Alan Charles Klein (born 29 June 1940) is an English singer-songwriter and musician.
He wrote the soundtrack for the stage play and film, What a Crazy World (1963).
In 1964, he released his only solo album, Well at Least It's British, that was re-released in 2008 by RPM Records.

In 1966 he went on tour as lead vocalist of The New Vaudeville Band.
